    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive production hinges on a clear frontrunner: **Tyler Freeman**. With a score of 68.67, he is our only \"Strong\" start, buoyed by an excellent matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez, whose xERA of 5.43 offers a prime opportunity for offensive production. The decision to slot **Tyler Freeman** into the #2 hole is bolstered by the 19% boost from the opposing SP\u2019s statistical profile, making him a high-floor play despite the volatility of a pending lineup. Conversely, we are navigating a difficult day for the rest of the infield. **Gleyber Torres** (51.25) presents a decent floor against Abel, but his score is suppressed by a 13% drag due to the platoon disadvantage. We are also monitoring **Gavin Sheets** (48.57) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (42.63), both of whom are currently in the \"Marginal\" category. **Geraldo Perdomo** faces a tough test against Nolan McLean, whose 3.04 xERA mandates caution, pulling his projection down significantly.\n\nOur bench strategy remains dictated by a mix of off-days and organizational adjustments. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Yainer Diaz** are unavailable due to scheduling, the lack of activity from **Lawrence Butler** is a notable absence from our active depth. **Gavin Sheets** essentially forced his way into the lineup as a \"Marginal\" start because we lacked a superior alternative with a confirmed role; had **Lawrence Butler** been active, the dynamic of our utility spots would have shifted drastically. Looking ahead, we need to remain vigilant regarding **Masyn Winn**, **Jonathan Aranda**, and **Jeremiah Jackson**, as their roles remain fluid. We are closely watching the weather and late-inning adjustments for **Bryson Stott**, **Will Smith**, **Taylor Ward**, **Matt Chapman**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Luis Arraez**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** to ensure we are maximizing our limited game caps while prioritizing the stolen base upside that remains the lifeblood of our strategy.",
